EXTRACTED VALUE: Sully looked back at the cave indecisively. "They'd want us to."
"Well, he's a deep one anyway. Look at his eyes."
"So do I. Remember the time he made us run slot-waggle-right for two solid hours in practice?"
"Would you be referring to me?" Myron asked.
“And a het. Where’s my brother? You’ll have to be a brother to me. No. Treat me as the child you never had.”
